Heat the oil in a wok or large frying pan and stir fry the garlic, chilli and ginger for one minute.Add the red pepper and pak choi and stir fry for a further minute.Add the prawns, soy sauce, honey and noodles and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until the prawns have turned pink and are cooked through.To serve, place into a serving dish, sprinkle over the coriander and garnish with lime wedges.